### TWENTY-THIRD KHA*ND*A.

1\. 'The Infinite (bhûman) <span
id="fr_322"></span>[1](sbe01159.htm#fn_320.md) is bliss. There is no bliss
in anything finite. Infinity only is bliss. This Infinity, however, we
must desire to understand.'

'Sir, I desire to understand it.'

